The paper deals with the construction of assume-guarantee specifications for multiple agents to cooperate, which involves logical reasoning and formal methods. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the goals assigned to each agent, which can be seen as a multi-agent system, making cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions fixpoint structures and time complexity, which are related to programming languages and compilers, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible sub-category. The paper deals with synchronous systems, which are a type of real-time systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a symbolic algorithm for constructing assume-guarantee specifications, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
